**Verdict: SHIP**

No correctness bug found in the reviewed diff. I do not see a path where `NEMOTRON_WS_SCHEDULER=1` and `NEMOTRON_WS_STEADY_SHADOW=0` can reach an inline `*enc_steady` deref.

**Findings**

- Null-safety: OK. `inline_enc_steady_ptr()` returns `nullptr` only for scheduler-on/shadow-off ([runtime.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/runtime.cpp:875)); the leaf uses scheduler when present ([session.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/session.cpp:2998)) and throws before both inline derefs in shadow and fallback branches ([session.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/session.cpp:2980), [session.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/session.cpp:3012)). `vad_stop` does not touch it, finalize uses only `finalize_loaders`, and flush paths only pass the pointer through to the same guarded leaf.

- Reorder: OK. Scheduler preload/build/warmup/start now completes before lane warmup ([runtime.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/runtime.cpp:784), [runtime.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/runtime.cpp:829)); that block depends on `finalize_loaders->shared_constants()`, not warmed lanes ([runtime.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/runtime.cpp:795)). Warmup passes `scheduler.get()` and shadow flag ([runtime.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/runtime.cpp:1129)).

- Admission safety: OK. Sync warmup still marks and publishes lanes before ctor return: all lanes in normal mode ([runtime.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/runtime.cpp:1329)), sync lanes in background mode ([runtime.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/runtime.cpp:1347)); admission provider is installed only after `SharedRuntime` construction ([ws_server.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/ws_server.cpp:1881)).

- Lifetime: OK. `scheduler`/`batched_steady` are destroyed before `finalize_loaders`, preserving borrowed shared constants ([runtime.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/runtime.cpp:1376)); `enc_steady_once` is inert and adjacent to `enc_steady` ([runtime.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/runtime.cpp:1374)). Memory logging only tests pointer presence, no deref ([runtime.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/runtime.cpp:901)).

- Lazy latency: OK. Valid scheduler-off/shadow modes eagerly call `ensure_inline_enc_steady()` during construction and log `INLINE_ENC_STEADY_LAZY_LOAD` ([runtime.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/runtime.cpp:749), [runtime.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/runtime.cpp:855)). Deploy mode returns null and never lazy-loads. No deadlock found with `enc_first_mutex`; valid lazy-use modes are already loaded before serving/warmup.

- Warmup/scope: OK. Shadow warmup now intentionally runs the shadow-compare path with both scheduler and inline available ([session.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/session.cpp:2980)); no byte/token numeric risk seen, because routing only chooses scheduler vs existing inline path.

What might be missed: invalid config `steady_shadow_enabled && !scheduler_enabled` loads inline before throwing ([runtime.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/runtime.cpp:749), [runtime.cpp](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/proj-2026-05-24-from-scratch-runtime/runtime/cpp/lib/session/runtime.cpp:777)). Not a valid serving-mode bug, but moving that validation earlier would avoid wasted startup work on misconfig. Also expect shadow warmup to add warmup-labeled shadow reports; that is a diagnostic behavior change, not a correctness regression.
